 Educational Background



B.A. in Economics 


Shiga University

                  Shiga University is a school.                




MBA 


University of California Berkeley - Haas School of Business

                  The Walter A. Haas School of Business, also known as the Haas School of Business or simply Haas, is one of 14 schools and colleges at the University of California, Berkeley.

The school runs a range of programs and is consistently ranked among the best in the country. Known for its small class size, academic rigor, and application selectivity, Haas is one of the most prestigious business schools in the world. It is the second oldest business school in the United States.                





 Career History



Managing Director & Head of Sunrise, Japan

                                    Current                


CLSA Capital Partners (Hong Kong) Ltd.


                  CLSA-HK is an activist investor following a growth-oriented investment approach and a thematic investment process. Focusing on Asia, the firm seeks to invest in companies with substantial latent growth potential. They aim to increase the value of their investments through active M&A strategies. They support management buy-outs of mid-sized companies, and engage in minority investment activities, growth capital funding and business-revitalization. CLSA-HK cooperates with management to increase corporate value by reinforcing the company's financial foundations and expanding profit opportunities in core businesses.The firm manages specialist equity funds focused on growth capital, Asian real estate, mid-market buyout opportunities in Japan, Asia's clean energy sector, and mezzanine debt financing for Asian buyouts. Investments themes include domestic demand, asset reflation, Japanese economic recovery, interregional trade and outsourcing of in-house logistics at small and medium-sized Japanese companies.                




Managing Director

                                    Current                


CLSA Capital Partners (Japan)


                  CLSA CPJ is an active, growth-oriented manager with a long-term investment capability which seeks to invest in well managed, high growth companies, real estate, buyout financing and mid-market buyouts.The firm invests in established businesses which are well-positioned to capitalize on the benefits of Japan's economic resurgence and which have management teams prepared to embrace a new partnership leading to growth and enhanced performance.CLSA CPJ considers investments in all sectors, particularly consumer products, food processing, healthcare, consumer retail, logistics and distribution, BPO and industrial manufacturing.The firm is active in providing growth capital for minority positions in high-growth corporations and expanding core businesses; mid-market buyouts and divisional spin-offs ; delisting of public companies whose market valuations are below fundamental values in order to allow for value creation through strategic, managerial, and governance guidance and private investment in public entities, where they follow a value-added approach including M&A assistance and corporate governance.Their managers act as partners with their portfolio companies, working actively with companies at the board of director level to provide financial and strategic guidelines while allowing management control of day-to-day operations.                




Managing Director-Head of Sunrise-Japan

                                    Current                


CLSA Sunrise Capital Fund


                  Founded in 2006, Sunrise Capital is a Japan dedicated private equity strategy focusing on investments in established mid-cap companies. Sunrise Capital supports domestic growth by providing strategic solutions for companies planning on Asian business expansion. Our sophisticated management platform leverages our wide breadth of experience and extensive Asian network.                




Senior Manager

                                    Prior                


The Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi Ltd. (New York Branch)


                  The Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi Ltd. provides commercial banking services.  The bank serves as the retail arm of The Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ (BTMU) in the United States. The company was established in 1996 and is based in New York, New York.                




Professional

                                    Prior                


The Carlyle Group LP (Corporate Private Equity)


                  The Carlyle Group LP (Corporate Private Equity) focuses either on a particular geography (Asia, Europe, Japan, Middle East and North Africa (MENA), South America, Sub-Saharan Africa or the United States) or a particular industry, such as financial services. The firm invests in aerospace, defense & government services, consumer & retail, energy, financial services, healthcare, industrial, real estate, technology & business services, telecommunications & media, and transportation.                





 Boards & Committees



Corporate Boards ▾




Outside Director

                    2014 - Current                  


BayCurrent Consulting, Inc.

                    BayCurrent Consulting, Inc. engages in the provision of consulting services. It offers Strategy Business Process Consulting, Information Technology (IT) Consulting, and System Integration. The Strategy Business Process Consulting covers company or business strategy, M&A alliances, digital strategy, turn-around, globalization, innovation, and marketing or sales strategy. The IT Consulting includes IT strategy, governance, organizational improvement, cost optimization, architecture, asset evaluation and talent development. The System Integration handles system design, development and infrastructure operation and maintenance. The company was founded on March 25, 1998 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.                  




Director

